text.section:
Promptly after an inmate is sentenced to the jurisdiction of the Division, the Division shall assemble an adequate case record for the inmate that includes:
a description of the inmate;
a photograph of the inmate;
the family history of the inmate;
any previous record of the inmate;
a summary of the facts of each case for which the inmate is serving a sentence; and
the results of the physical, mental, and educational examination of the inmate required under subsection (b) of this section.
